
Overview of noun boldness

The noun boldness has 3 senses (first 1 from tagged texts)
                                       
1. (1) boldness, daring, hardiness, hardihood -- (the trait of being willing to undertake things that involve risk or danger; "the proposal required great boldness"; "the plan required great hardiness of heart")
2. boldness, nerve, brass, face, cheek -- (impudent aggressiveness; "I couldn't believe her boldness"; "he had the effrontery to question my honesty")
3. boldness, strikingness -- (the quality of standing out strongly and distinctly)
